==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Melaniline
<hw>Me*lan"i*line</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A complex nitrogenous hydrocarbon obtained artificially (as by the
action of cyanogen chloride on aniline) as a white, crystalline
substance; -- called also <altname>diphenyl
guanidin</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Melanin</ent>⟦br⟧
